sql:
SELECT size 
FROM product_sizes 
WHERE stock_quantity = (SELECT MAX(stock_quantity) FROM product_sizes);

SELECT p.product_name, p.price
FROM products p
INNER JOIN product_sizes ps ON p.product_id = ps.product_id;

external_knowledge:
- "pricier items" refers to products with a price greater than 100;
- "average quantity in stock" means the average stock quantity across all sizes in each category;
- "currently in stock somewhere" means there is at least one size of the product that has a stock quantity greater than zero.

sql:
SELECT brands.brand_name
FROM brands
WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM products WHERE products.brand_id = brands.brand_id);

external_knowledge:
- 'esteemed brand' refers to brand_id = 1;
- 'main region' refers to region_id = 0;
- 'popular items' implies the products are in demand but, in context, simply means the products have a stock quantity greater than 0.
